<DocsLayout
  title="Install hitlimit - npm Rate Limiter for Node.js, Express, NestJS, Bun"
  description="Install hitlimit rate limiting package via npm, pnpm, yarn, or bun. Quick setup guide for Express.js, NestJS, Bun.serve, and Elysia applications with memory, SQLite, or Redis stores."
  keywords="npm install hitlimit, rate limit npm, install rate limiter, express rate limit install, nestjs throttler install, bun rate limit, hitlimit-bun install, nodejs rate limiter setup"
>
  <h1>Installation</h1>

  <p>Install hitlimit using your preferred package manager.</p>

  <h2 id="nodejs">Node.js</h2>

  <Tabs
    tabs={[
      { label: 'npm', content: 'npm install @joint-ops/hitlimit' },
      { label: 'pnpm', content: 'pnpm add @joint-ops/hitlimit' },
      { label: 'yarn', content: 'yarn add @joint-ops/hitlimit' },
      { label: 'bun', content: 'bun add @joint-ops/hitlimit' },
    ]}
  />

  <h2 id="bun">Bun (Optimized)</h2>

  <p>For Bun applications, use the Bun-optimized package with native SQLite:</p>

  <Tabs
    tabs={[
      { label: 'bun', content: 'bun add @joint-ops/hitlimit-bun' },
    ]}
  />

  <h2 id="stores">Optional Store Packages</h2>

  <p>Install additional stores as needed:</p>

  <h3>Redis Store</h3>
  <p>Install the <code>ioredis</code> peer dependency to use the Redis store:</p>
  <Tabs
    tabs={[
      { label: 'npm', content: 'npm install ioredis' },
      { label: 'pnpm', content: 'pnpm add ioredis' },
      { label: 'yarn', content: 'yarn add ioredis' },
    ]}
  />

  <h3>SQLite Store (Node.js)</h3>
  <Tabs
    tabs={[
      { label: 'npm', content: 'npm install better-sqlite3' },
      { label: 'pnpm', content: 'pnpm add better-sqlite3' },
      { label: 'yarn', content: 'yarn add better-sqlite3' },
    ]}
  />

  <h2 id="requirements">Requirements</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Node.js</strong>: v18.0.0 or higher</li>
    <li><strong>Bun</strong>: v1.0.0 or higher</li>
    <li><strong>TypeScript</strong>: v5.0 or higher (optional)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="next-steps">Next Steps</h2>

  <p>Now that you have hitlimit installed, head over to the <a href="/docs/quick-start">Quick Start</a> guide to set up your first rate limiter.</p>
</DocsLayout>
